text: László Cseh Sr. (14 March 1952 - 24 August 2020) was a Hungarian swimmer. He competed at the 1968 Summer Olympics and the 1972 Summer Olympics. His son, László Cseh, is a six time Olympic medalist. Cseh Sr. died on 24 August 2020 in Budapest, aged 68. ==References== Category:1952 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Hungarian swimmers Category:Sportspeople from Budapest Category:Olympians for Hungary
